      <h1 class="blog-title">Is It Safe to Put Your Baby Online? How a Legacy Odyssey Website Stays Private</h1>

      <p class="blog-meta">Privacy &amp; Safety &nbsp;&bull;&nbsp; 5 min read</p>

      <div class="blog-body">

        <p>If you've ever hesitated before posting a photo of your child, you already understand the question behind this post. You want the people who love your child to watch them grow — and you don't want your child to be public, searchable, or out there for strangers. Those two wishes can feel like they're at odds. With Legacy Odyssey, they aren't.</p>

        <p>A Legacy Odyssey Website isn't just a baby book. It's your child's whole life journey, on a website that's genuinely theirs — and privacy is built into how that website works, from the day you claim it. Here's exactly how.</p>

        <hr>

        <h2>It's private by default</h2>

        <p>Every Legacy Odyssey Website is password-protected before anyone can see a thing. A visitor who goes to your child's address is met with a password prompt first — no photos, no name, no birth details until they enter the password you set.</p>

        <p>There's no "public" switch to forget to turn off. And if a site somehow had no password set, it stays locked rather than opening — the system is built to fail safe, so a Legacy Odyssey Website can't accidentally become public.</p>

        <hr>

        <h2>You decide exactly who gets in</h2>

        <p>You control the password, and you choose who to share it with. Nobody sees your child's website without it.</p>

        <p>When you're ready to share, you don't have to pass the password around by text. From your contacts, you can send each person their own private link that opens the website without a password on their end — no account to create, nothing to download. And if you ever remove someone from your contacts, their private link stops working. Access is something you give, and something you can take back.</p>

        <hr>

        <h2>It's not in Google</h2>

        <p>This is the part most parents ask about: will my child turn up in a search?</p>

        <p>No. Every Legacy Odyssey Website is deliberately kept out of search engines. Search engines are told not to index or store your child's site — in two independent ways at once: an instruction sent with every page (a header that search engines obey), and a "noindex" tag on every page itself. Either one alone does the job; together they're belt-and-suspenders.</p>

        <p>Your child's website is somewhere people go because you invited them — not something a stranger stumbles onto in a search.</p>

        <p><em>(The only public example anywhere is our own demo, which uses a made-up child so we have something to show visitors. Real customers' websites are never public.)</em></p>

        <hr>

        <h2>Your information is handled with care</h2>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>Encrypted connection.</strong> Every page loads over a secure, encrypted (HTTPS) connection.</li>
          <li><strong>Stored securely.</strong> Your photos and words are kept with an established platform (Supabase) that encrypts data at rest and keeps regular backups.</li>
          <li><strong>Never sold.</strong> We do not sell, rent, or trade your personal information — ever. We share data only with the service providers needed to run the website (hosting, payments, email), never with data brokers.</li>
        </ul>

        <hr>

        <h2>Built with children's privacy in mind</h2>

        <p>Only an adult can create and manage an account. A Legacy Odyssey Website is made for parents and guardians, consistent with the U.S. Children's Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA) and, where it applies, GDPR protections for children's data. The content about your child is yours — provided by you, and controlled by you.</p>

        <hr>

        <h2>You stay in control — always</h2>

        <ul>
          <li>Change the password whenever you like.</li>
          <li>Remove anyone's access.</li>
          <li>Ask us to delete your data — you can request deletion at any time. And if you ever cancel, you have up to a year to come back before your content is removed, so nothing disappears the moment a subscription lapses.</li>
        </ul>

        <hr>

        <h2>The honest part</h2>

        <p>No online tool is more private than the password behind it. A Legacy Odyssey Website is as private as you keep it: share the password with the people you trust, and it stays a quiet corner of the internet meant for exactly them.</p>

        <p>That's the whole idea — a place that's truly your child's, that the right people can visit and no one else can find.</p>

